# 03-backend-typescript-rules.mdc

---
description: Backend implementation standards
globs:
- "backend/**"
- "server/**"
---

Backend is the authoritative business layer.

Responsibilities:

- Business rules
- Validation
- Authentication
- Authorization
- Transactions
- Integrations

Rules:

- Keep controllers thin.
- Keep business logic in domain services.
- Use dependency injection.
- Use typed interfaces.
- Validate all external input.
- Avoid exposing database models directly.

Every feature should define:

- Domain model
- Service layer
- API contract
- Validation
- Tests
